    "hotel_url": "https://www.agoda.com/atrium-hotel-heathrow_2/hotel/london-gb.html",
    "name": "Atrium Hotel Heathrow",
    "detail": "Pros: New building Clean Rooms a bit more spacious than London hotels Gym in basement new & functional Spa pool and jacuzzi looked really nice especially the pool. (I did not use because smelled weird and the jacuzzi had family with kids splashing and being noisy. ) After 7pm kids are not allowed but you just don't know what they left behind in the water....... Location: very close to Hatton cross (one tube stop from airport central). However be advised if you have heavy suitcases Hatton cross exit has 2 staircases. No lift or escalator. To get to Heathrow use free 285 bus. The x26 will charge. The hotel also has a shuttle but they charge. 15mins Con: availibility of food. There is no tesco etc within walking distance just an overpriced garage. The hotel has a coffee bar and restaurant both were almost empty. I did not eat here so can't comment on food but the prices were very expensive for a basic hotel. OK as stop over if price right. ",
